relevant_findings.general: Alert and in no apparent distress

relevant_findings.ent: Ears and nose without visible erythema, masses, or trauma. Oropharynx without visible lesion, erythema or exudate
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Heart regular, no murmur, no S3, no S4. No JVD

relevant_findings.ct: Bibasilar atelectasis. No large pleural effusion or pericardial effusion. Coronary artery calcifications are moderate. The pancreas shows a 1.1 x 1.5 cm hypodense cystic lesion that has increased in size compared to previous and soft tissue stranding about the pancreatic head and body. Subtle peripheral hypodensity in the spleen likely reflects a prior infarct, new from prior exam. Mild right renal cortical scarring. Multiple bilateral renal cystic structures measure up to 2.6 x 2.4 cm in the right upper pole kidney.

changes_over_time.pancreatic_lesion: Increased in size from 0.6 x 0.7 cm previously to 1.1 x 1.5 cm
changes_over_time.spleen: Subtle peripheral hypodensity new from prior exam
